    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "summary": "Imam al-Baqir, as transmitted through Imam al-Sadiq, instructs that the funeral prayer should be performed for every Muslim who dies - anyone who faces the qibla (direction of prayer toward Mecca). The judgment of their inner faith and deeds is left entirely to Allah. This teaching was given in the context of early Islamic debates about who deserved funeral rites, establishing that external Muslim identity through facing the qibla was sufficient grounds for the prayer, without passing judgment on the deceased's personal beliefs or sins.",
        "key_terms": {
          "أَهْلِ الْقِبْلَةِ": "People of the qibla - those who face Mecca in prayer, i.e. Muslims",
          "حِسَابُهُ": "His reckoning/judgment - the accounting of deeds before Allah",
          "صَلِّ": "Pray (the funeral prayer) - specifically the salat al-janaza"
        },
        "seo_question": "What did Imam al-Baqir say about performing funeral prayer for Muslims regardless of their standing?"
      },
